{
  "verses": [
    {
      "verse_num": "1",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Blessed are those whose ways are blameless, who walk according to Yahweh’s law."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "2",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Blessed are those who keep his statutes, who seek him with their whole heart."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "3",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Yes, they do nothing wrong. They walk in his ways."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "4",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "You have commanded your precepts, that we should fully obey them."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "5",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Oh that my ways were steadfastto obey your statutes!"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "6",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Then I wouldn’t be disappointed, when I consider all of your commandments."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "7",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I will give thanks to you with uprightness of heart, when I learn your righteous judgments."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "8",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I will observe your statutes. Don’t utterly forsake me. BETH"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "9",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "How can a young man keep his way pure? By living according to your word."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "10",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "With my whole heart I have sought you. Don’t let me wander from your commandments."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "11",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I have hidden your word in my heart, that I might not sin against you."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "12",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Blessed are you, Yahweh. Teach me your statutes."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "13",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "With my lips, I have declared all the ordinances of your mouth."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "14",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I have rejoiced in the way of your testimonies, as much as in all riches."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "15",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I will meditate on your precepts, and consider your ways."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "16",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I will delight myself in your statutes. I will not forget your word. GIMEL"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "17",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Do good to your servant. I will live and I will obey your word."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "18",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Open my eyes, that I may see wondrous things out of your law."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "19",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I am a stranger on the earth. Don’t hide your commandments from me."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "20",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "My soul is consumed with longing for your ordinances at all times."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "21",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "You have rebuked the proud who are cursed, who wander from your commandments."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "22",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Take reproach and contempt away from me, for I have kept your statutes."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "23",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Though princes sit and slander me, your servant will meditate on your statutes."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "24",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Indeed your statutes are my delight, and my counselors. DALETH"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "25",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "My soul is laid low in the dust. Revive me according to your word!"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "26",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I declared my ways, and you answered me. Teach me your statutes."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "27",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Let me understand the teaching of your precepts! Then I will meditate on your wondrous works."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "28",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "My soul is weary with sorrow; strengthen me according to your word."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "29",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Keep me from the way of deceit. Grant me your law graciously!"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "30",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I have chosen the way of truth. I have set your ordinances before me."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "31",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I cling to your statutes, Yahweh. Don’t let me be disappointed."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "32",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I run in the path of your commandments, for you have set my heart free. HE"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "33",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Teach me, Yahweh, the way of your statutes. I will keep them to the end."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "34",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Give me understanding, and I will keep your law. Yes, I will obey it with my whole heart."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "35",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Direct me in the path of your commandments, for I delight in them."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "36",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Turn my heart toward your statutes, not toward selfish gain."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "37",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Turn my eyes away from looking at worthless things. Revive me in your ways."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "38",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Fulfill your promise to your servant, that you may be feared."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "39",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Take away my disgrace that I dread, for your ordinances are good."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "40",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Behold, I long for your precepts! Revive me in your righteousness. VAV"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "41",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Let your loving kindness also come to me, Yahweh, your salvation, according to your word."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "42",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "So I will have an answer for him who reproaches me, for I trust in your word."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "43",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Don’t snatch the word of truth out of my mouth, for I put my hope in your ordinances."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "44",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "So I will obey your law continually, forever and ever."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "45",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I will walk in liberty, for I have sought your precepts."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "46",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I will also speak of your statutes before kings, and will not be disappointed."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "47",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I will delight myself in your commandments, because I love them."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "48",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I reach out my hands for your commandments, which I love. I will meditate on your statutes. ZAYIN"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "49",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Remember your word to your servant, because you gave me hope."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "50",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "This is my comfort in my affliction, for your word has revived me."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "51",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "The arrogant mock me excessively, but I don’t swerve from your law."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "52",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I remember your ordinances of old, Yahweh, and have comforted myself."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "53",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Indignation has taken hold on me, because of the wicked who forsake your law."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "54",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Your statutes have been my songsin the house where I live."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "55",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I have remembered your name, Yahweh, in the night, and I obey your law."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "56",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "This is my way, that I keep your precepts. HETH"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "57",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Yahweh is my portion. I promised to obey your words."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "58",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I sought your favor with my whole heart. Be merciful to me according to your word."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "59",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I considered my ways, and turned my steps to your statutes."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "60",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I will hurry, and not delay, to obey your commandments."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "61",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "The ropes of the wicked bind me, but I won’t forget your law."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "62",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "At midnight I will rise to give thanks to you, because of your righteous ordinances."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "63",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I am a friend of all those who fear you, of those who observe your precepts."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "64",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "The earth is full of your loving kindness, Yahweh. Teach me your statutes. TETH"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "65",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "You have treated your servant well, according to your word, Yahweh."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "66",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Teach me good judgment and knowledge, for I believe in your commandments."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "67",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Before I was afflicted, I went astray; but now I observe your word."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "68",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "You are good, and do good. Teach me your statutes."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "69",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "The proud have smeared a lie upon me. With my whole heart, I will keep your precepts."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "70",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Their heart is as callous as the fat, but I delight in your law."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "71",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "It is good for me that I have been afflicted, that I may learn your statutes."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "72",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "The law of your mouth is better to me than thousands of pieces of gold and silver. YODH"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "73",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Your hands have made me and formed me. Give me understanding, that I may learn your commandments."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "74",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Those who fear you will see me and be glad, because I have put my hope in your word."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "75",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Yahweh, I know that your judgments are righteous, that in faithfulness you have afflicted me."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "76",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Please let your loving kindness be for my comfort, according to your word to your servant."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "77",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Let your tender mercies come to me, that I may live; for your law is my delight."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "78",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Let the proud be disappointed, for they have overthrown me wrongfully. I will meditate on your precepts."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "79",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Let those who fear you turn to me. They will know your statutes."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "80",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Let my heart be blameless toward your decrees, that I may not be disappointed. KAPF"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "81",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "My soul faints for your salvation. I hope in your word."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "82",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "My eyes fail for your word. I say, "
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "When will you comfort me?",
          "speaker": "Unknown"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "83",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "For I have become like a wineskin in the smoke. I don’t forget your statutes."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "84",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "How many are the days of your servant? When will you execute judgment on those who persecute me?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "85",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "The proud have dug pits for me, contrary to your law."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "86",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "All of your commandments are faithful. They persecute me wrongfully."
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Help me!"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "87",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "They had almost wiped me from the earth, but I didn’t forsake your precepts."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "88",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Preserve my life according to your loving kindness, so I will obey the statutes of your mouth. LAMEDH"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "89",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Yahweh, your word is settled in heaven forever."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "90",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Your faithfulness is to all generations. You have established the earth, and it remains."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "91",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Your laws remain to this day, for all things serve you."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "92",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Unless your law had been my delight, I would have perished in my affliction."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "93",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I will never forget your precepts, for with them, you have revived me."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "94",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I am yours. Save me, for I have sought your precepts."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "95",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "The wicked have waited for me, to destroy me. I will consider your statutes."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "96",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I have seen a limit to all perfection, but your commands are boundless. MEM"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "97",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "How I love your law! It is my meditation all day."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "98",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Your commandments make me wiser than my enemies, for your commandments are always with me."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "99",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I have more understanding than all my teachers, for your testimonies are my meditation."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "100",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I understand more than the aged, because I have kept your precepts."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "101",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I have kept my feet from every evil way, that I might observe your word."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "102",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I have not turned away from your ordinances, for you have taught me."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "103",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "How sweet are your promises to my taste, more than honey to my mouth!"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "104",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Through your precepts, I get understanding; therefore I hate every false way. NUN"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "105",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Your word is a lamp to my feet, and a light for my path."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "106",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I have sworn, and have confirmed it, that I will obey your righteous ordinances."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "107",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I am afflicted very much. Revive me, Yahweh, according to your word."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "108",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Accept, I beg you, the willing offerings of my mouth. Yahweh, teach me your ordinances."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "109",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "My soul is continually in my hand, yet I won’t forget your law."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "110",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "The wicked have laid a snare for me, yet I haven’t gone astray from your precepts."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "111",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I have taken your testimonies as a heritage forever, for they are the joy of my heart."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "112",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I have set my heart to perform your statutes forever, even to the end. SAMEKH"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "113",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I hate double-minded men, but I love your law."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "114",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "You are my hiding place and my shield. I hope in your word."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "115",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Depart from me, you evildoers, that I may keep the commandments of my God."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "116",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Uphold me according to your word, that I may live. Let me not be ashamed of my hope."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "117",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Hold me up, and I will be safe, and will have respect for your statutes continually."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "118",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "You reject all those who stray from your statutes, for their deceit is in vain."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "119",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "You put away all the wicked of the earth like dross. Therefore I love your testimonies."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "120",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "My flesh trembles for fear of you. I am afraid of your judgments. AYIN"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "121",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I have done what is just and righteous. Don’t leave me to my oppressors."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "122",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Ensure your servant’s well-being. Don’t let the proud oppress me."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "123",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "My eyes fail looking for your salvation, for your righteous word."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "124",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Deal with your servant according to your loving kindness. Teach me your statutes."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "125",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I am your servant. Give me understanding, that I may know your testimonies."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "126",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "It is time to act, Yahweh, for they break your law."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "127",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Therefore I love your commandments more than gold, yes, more than pure gold."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "128",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Therefore I consider all of your precepts to be right. I hate every false way. PE"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "129",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Your testimonies are wonderful, therefore my soul keeps them."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "130",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "The entrance of your words gives light. It gives understanding to the simple."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "131",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I opened my mouth wide and panted, for I longed for your commandments."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "132",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Turn to me, and have mercy on me, as you always do to those who love your name."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "133",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Establish my footsteps in your word. Don’t let any iniquity have dominion over me."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "134",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Redeem me from the oppression of man, so I will observe your precepts."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "135",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Make your face shine on your servant. Teach me your statutes."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "136",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Streams of tears run down my eyes, because they don’t observe your law. TZADHE"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "137",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "You are righteous, Yahweh. Your judgments are upright."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "138",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "You have commanded your statutes in righteousness. They are fully trustworthy."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "139",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "My zeal wears me out, because my enemies ignore your words."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "140",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Your promises have been thoroughly tested, and your servant loves them."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "141",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I am small and despised. I don’t forget your precepts."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "142",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Your righteousness is an everlasting righteousness. Your law is truth."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "143",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Trouble and anguish have taken hold of me. Your commandments are my delight."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "144",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Your testimonies are righteous forever. Give me understanding, that I may live. QOPH"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "145",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I have called with my whole heart. Answer me, Yahweh!"
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I will keep your statutes."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "146",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I have called to you. Save me! I will obey your statutes."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "147",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I rise before dawn and cry for help. I put my hope in your words."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "148",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "My eyes stay open through the night watches, that I might meditate on your word."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "149",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Hear my voice according to your loving kindness. Revive me, Yahweh, according to your ordinances."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "150",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "They draw near who follow after wickedness. They are far from your law."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "151",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "You are near, Yahweh. All your commandments are truth."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "152",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Of old I have known from your testimonies, that you have founded them forever. RESH"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "153",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Consider my affliction, and deliver me, for I don’t forget your law."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "154",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Plead my cause, and redeem me! Revive me according to your promise."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "155",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Salvation is far from the wicked, for they don’t seek your statutes."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "156",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Great are your tender mercies, Yahweh. Revive me according to your ordinances."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "157",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Many are my persecutors and my adversaries. I haven’t swerved from your testimonies."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "158",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I look at the faithless with loathing, because they don’t observe your word."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "159",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Consider how I love your precepts. Revive me, Yahweh, according to your loving kindness."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "160",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "All of your words are truth. Every one of your righteous ordinances endures forever. SIN AND SHIN"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "161",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Princes have persecuted me without a cause, but my heart stands in awe of your words."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "162",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I rejoice at your word, as one who finds great plunder."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "163",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I hate and abhor falsehood. I love your law."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "164",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Seven times a day, I praise you, because of your righteous ordinances."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "165",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Those who love your law have great peace. Nothing causes them to stumble."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "166",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I have hoped for your salvation, Yahweh. I have done your commandments."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "167",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "My soul has observed your testimonies. I love them exceedingly."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "168",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I have obeyed your precepts and your testimonies, for all my ways are before you. TAV"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "169",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Let my cry come before you, Yahweh. Give me understanding according to your word."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "170",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Let my supplication come before you. Deliver me according to your word."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "171",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Let my lips utter praise, for you teach me your statutes."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "172",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Let my tongue sing of your word, for all your commandments are righteousness."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "173",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Let your hand be ready to help me, for I have chosen your precepts."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "174",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I have longed for your salvation, Yahweh. Your law is my delight."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "175",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Let my soul live, that I may praise you. Let your ordinances help me."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "176",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I have gone astray like a lost sheep. Seek your servant, for I don’t forget your commandments."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    }
  ]
}